w:r.w:t: : Finding the most influential nodes in a network using Betweenness Centrality
Compute the shortest-path betweenness centrality for nodes.
is the sum of the fraction of all-pairs shortest paths that pass through
is the number of those paths passing through some node
The function betweenness centrality accepts a bunch of nodes and computes

the contribution of those nodes to the betweenness centrality of the whole network. Here on contrary to worksharing approach followed by Brande, we used SPMD approach to distribute the same instruction set among the cores and we compute multiple nodes betweenness centrality at each unit point of time in the whole network using the pool class in multiprocessor library.
